declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'-/-'
Handle *`zsh` subshell* (i.e., child shells forked from other shells, typically
using `(...)` and `$(...)` syntax) aliases.
-/-

# ....................{ TESTERS                            }....................
# Integer global ${ZSH_SUBSHELL} expands to the current subshell depth or 0 if
# the current shell is *NOT* a subshell. Hence, the current shell is a subshell
# if and only if such global is nonzero.
declare_alias_with_stdin\
    '[status: boolean] is_shell_subshell(void)'\
    '(( ZSH_SUBSHELL ))' <<'/---'
Return success if the current shell is a *subshell* (i.e., a child shell forked
from another shell, typically using `(...)` and `$(...)` syntax).
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
